1. NETWORKING


netstat -ano > netstat.txt	Active connections & listening ports with PID.
Capture a baseline of open ports.

ping -n 5 8.8.8.8	Simple reachability test.
Verify that the NIC works even if DNS fails.

tracert 8.8.8.8 > trace.txt	Route path to a host.
Helpful if you later need to compare routing changes.

nslookup <hostname>	DNS lookup.
Record expected IPs for critical hosts (e.g., internal servers).


2. SECURITY AND PERMISSIONS

sfc /scannow	System File Checker – verifies and repairs protected Windows files. 
Store network layout before moving a machine.

icacls <path> /save aclfile /t	Export ACLs recursively.
Back up permissions before moving a folder to another machine.

icacls <path> /restore aclfile	Restore previously saved ACLs.
Re‑apply original permissions after a restore.

cipher /w:<folder>	Securely wipes free space (overwrites deleted data).
Clean a drive before handing it off or repurposing it.

whoami /all > whoami.txt	Shows user token groups & privileges.
Document the current user’s rights for audit purposes.


3. PACKAGE MANAGEMENT (incase of a portable package manager present)

winget export -o packages.json	Export list of installed apps (requires Winget).
Store packages.json in your repo; later you can reinstall with winget import packages.json.

choco list -lo > choco-list.txt	List locally installed Chocolatey packages.
Same idea as Winget – keep a manifest for re‑creation.

`powershell -Command "Get-AppxPackage	Export-Clixml -Path appx.xml"
Export all Store apps.


4. MISC COMMANDS

fsutil dirty query C:
Checks if the volume is marked “dirty” (needs chkdisk).

powercfg /batteryreport /output "%USERPROFILE%\battery-report.html"
Generates a detailed battery health report (great for laptops).

tasklist > tasks.txt
Captures a snapshot of running processes.

wmic os get Caption,Version,BuildNumber,OSArchitecture /format:list > osinfo.txt
Saves OS version & architecture

reg export HKLM\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Uninstall uninstall.reg
Exports list of installed programs from the registry.

